article.headline: Hampton 85, Howard 79
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Jeff Granger hit six 3-pointers and scored 31 points and Hampton used an 11-4 run to pull away late for an 85-79 victory against Howard on Saturday. The Pirates (12-15, 10-6 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), who opened the game on a 22-7 run, made the burst after Howard closed to 63-60 with 4:59 remaining. James Wilkinson scored 23 for the Bison (6-19, 4-12). Seye Aluko added 16 and Will Gant and Bilal Russell each scored 14. Gant was 4-for-5 from 3-point territory. Devin Green added 16 points and Bruce Brown 12 for the Pirates, who were 10-for-10 from the free throw line in the final 1:03. David Johnson had nine rebounds.
